Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Chris Woakes draws first blood on Day 3! In the channel outside off, on a good length, Mitchell Marsh looks to leave this delivery. He fails to get his glove out of the way and the ball comes off his gloves on its way to the keeper. Jonny Bairstow behind the wicket pouches it safely and England go up in unison. Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Mark Wood joins in on the act and Australia are now 7 wickets down! Bends his back and directs a bumper at the left shoulder of the batter, Mitchell Starc gets himself into an awkward position and is unable to fend this one well. The ball climbs on him and lobs behind square on the leg side. Harry Brook from short leg and Jonny Bairstow sprint towards the ball.
